name":"Carrie Reed","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/91279804"},{"created_at":"2014-04-30T20:45:58Z","content":"Freedom to learn!","like_count":2,"author_name":"Brett Ott","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/91280858"},{"created_at":"2014-04-30T18:11:58Z","content":"Women and girls should not be afraid to learn. They should be able to be safe in schools. That no one is going in to help is horrendous. If this happened in the United States agents would have been dispatched ages ago. ","like_count":2,"author_name":"Meris Mullaley","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/12386650"},{"created_at":"2014-05-07T23:50:42Z","content":"No one should be denied the freedom to learn.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Anthony Pacaro","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/92046114"},{"created_at":"2014-05-08T04:53:24Z","content":"All developed nations must take a stand now and get these girls and bring justice to their captors.  If we do nothing, this will become to the new way to bully governments and citizens and we can not accept that in any way, shape or form.  Do something NOW!","like_count":1,"author_name":"Dianna David","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2137274"},{"created_at":"2014-05-08T01:02:27Z","content":"This is a crime against all of our human rights.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Barbara Coon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/92065650"},{"created_at":"2014-05-08T00:57:59Z","content":"We cannot stand for militants to deprive these girls of education! Educating girls worldwide is the key to our world's future.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Shelby Johnson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/13065760"},{"created_at":"2014-05-08T05:01:51Z","content":"All people are important in God's eyes \u2013 especially children. We, as citizens and inhabitants of this shared world, have an obligation to fight for each other and to make this already difficult life a little less hard. If my sister or daughter or neighbor was missing, I would want someone to sign a petition to bring them home. These little girls deserve the same! ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Tiana Lewis","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/92119995"},{"created_at":"2014-05-08T00:40:04Z","content":"No child should be taken from their family.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Jamilah  Henry","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/6471146"},{"created_at":"2014-04-30T16:02:29Z","content":"Because I value black girls.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Fallon Wilson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/39915754"},{"created_at":"2014-05-07T23:11:38Z","content":"To help the girls to return home to their Families!  No one should be sold as slaves, in any country! ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Teresa Silcox","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/92042238"},{"created_at":"2014-05-08T00:24:08Z","content":"Please. Give me a reason to be proud of America again. Show all our children we will not tolerate them being abused, we will protect them.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Cathy McDowell","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/27341996"},{"created_at":"2014-05-08T00:20:30Z","content":"I'm a girl.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Brook Cosby","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/357463"},{"created_at":"2014-04-30T15:00:43Z","content":"This tragedy deserves as much attention as other international tragedies such as the Malaysian airplane that has been missing for weeks. We must act now.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Omoro Omoighe","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/91242118"},{"created_at":"2014-05-08T02:33:50Z","content":"Its is wrong, These girls need to be safely with their families. Not being held against their will and used.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Desiree Wade","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/92090368"},{"created_at":"2014-05-08T01:29:09Z","content":"No one, male or female of any age, should be stolen, abducted, sold, traded, abused, raped, treated like property, less than property, or victimized - EVER. This is about human rights. This is about terrorism. This is a terrorist act. Whether or not it was committed against Americans, it doesn\u2019t matter. Just because it wasn\u2019t on our soil and it didn\u2019t involve our citizens, doesn\u2019t mean that this won\u2019t happen in our country. The world is a global community now. Nothing is isolated. And if it happens to one, it happens to all. It is our duty to protect the innocence of the world, to help grow it and nurture it, not condone the abuse and destruction of it by turning a blind eye. If we do not help these girls, if we let the evil of this world destroy them by forcing them into a life of abuse, rape and horrors we cannot even begin to imagine, then we are no better than that evil. Do the right thing: Bring Back Our Girls.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Jennifer Morris","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/92072408"},{"created_at":"2014-05-08T02:10:57Z","content":"Because I care about the rights of all humans, not just americans. All people have the right to basic education and safety. ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Josiah Finley","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/92084288"},{"created_at":"2014-05-05T09:22:09Z","content":"it is just unfair","like_count":0,"author_name":"ROMY K","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/71658160"},{"created_at":"2014-05-10T06:09:57Z","content":"I feel strongly that this is a terrible thing to have happened. I'd be worried sick if any if these girls were related to me. I hope they're found alive and safe.","like_count":0,"author_name":"David Currie","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/46067135"},{"created_at":"2014-05-07T00:01:59Z","content":"No girl should be bought for $12 as a consequence of seeking education.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Christi Davis","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/91837660"},{"created_at":"2014-05-04T21:34:48Z","content":"Because I am also female and cannot believe that this kind of thinking is still going on in 2014.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Angela Miller","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/91624952"},{"created_at":"2014-05-02T00:31:35Z","content":"These girls are our girls. We need to bring them back. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Annemarie  Harris","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/929496"},{"created_at":"2014-05-13T10:39:07Z","content":"Because it's staggering that this can happen, without international outrage. Just imagine that these were American, or Belgian girls...","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ivo Delrue","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/93989780"},{"created_at":"2014-05-04T03:13:29Z","content":"human trafficing is a global problem that we need to stop the exploting of children making it crime punishable by death!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Alicia Anderson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/91576135"},{"created_at":"2014-04-27T06:40:37Z","content":"Because at there age they will be made sex toy and slaves in the terrorist camp.There release is very vital to every God fearing parents.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Auwalu Umoru","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/90915813"},{"created_at":"2014-05-05T18:37:00Z","content":"I work with a youth leadership program in Guatemala.  Still boys are chosen over girls to go to school if the family does not have enough money.  We have to have a stronger voice for girls.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lisa Doherty","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/91696575"},{"created_at":"2014-05-01T18:34:43Z","content":"Because something needs to be done. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Shane Taylor","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/29974728"},{"created_at":"2014-05-06T22:24:30Z","content":"What if this was your daughter?","like_count":0,"author_name":"Rob Nash","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/30636204"},{"created_at":"2014-05-03T13:47:38Z","content":"Sometimes there isn't much we can do but of we are not physically present when a crisis arises but we should not turn a blind. This is bringing attention to an autrocity that the whole world should be fighting against ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Tiffani Young","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/91534263"},{"created_at":"2014-05-05T09:44:59Z","content":"Bring back our girls, they are our future.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sonia  Lemord","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/13685129"},{"created_at":"2014-05-01T23:11:02Z","content":"This issue is important to me because I am a woman, a mother, and a human being.  Sometimes the world's problems seem too large and far away to do anything. I think of these girls having just finished their Physics exam, and being kidnapped, and I feel that maybe looking into this and the world pooling its efforts to get them back is something we can actually accomplish together, against the darker forces in the world.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Hilde Kaiser","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/55998033"},{"created_at":"2014-05-10T02:50:20Z","content":"This could be any one of our daughters.  This travesty is as horrendous as it comes. Please MAKE THIS A PRIORITY.  If it takes military action do it. take 1/3 of the resources utilized in looking for Osama Bin ladin. This is just ONE STEP, but instead of adults, its CHILDREN the terrorists are attacking! This is heinous, it is Global, and it should be ENDED IMMEDIATELY!","like_count":0,"author_name":"jacqueline  rogers","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7891522"},{"created_at":"2014-05-12T09:08:23Z","content":"I am working in an african country and see with my own eyes how important education is especially for girls in this countries. What has happened should be a sign for the world to stand up for the right of girls!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Susanne Mayer","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/93588708"},{"created_at":"2014-05-02T15:59:51Z","content":"because their action is inhumane..","like_count":0,"author_name":"christopher  Raymond","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/28032023"},{"created_at":"2014-05-07T19:00:59Z","content":"My Brethren.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Antonio Toro","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/80021982"},{"created_at":"2014-05-06T04:35:21Z","content":"These girls are the future they need to be saved, its inhumane to trade on human in the 21st century!!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Natacha Mikolo","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/91739971"},{"created_at":"2014-05-09T23:09:24Z","content":"The well being of these girls is a concern of mine. I don't think any girl should go through such atrocity, and the fact that this happened to 230 girls makes it worse. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sebastian Gallegos","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/92935908"},{"created_at":"2014-05-05T20:23:15Z","content":"I am a mother, a daughter, a sister, and above all, a person who believes in freedom and equality. I feel for these poor girls. We need to find them and bring them home!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Genevieve Janeczek","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78792360"},{"created_at":"2014-05-06T19:36:23Z","content":"No human being should be forced into human trafficking.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Dawn Johnston","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/91801370"},{"created_at":"2014-05-01T05:27:59Z","content":"I am a teacher, a mother, a woman, alive on this planet...this should be of the utmost importance to every single human being.  Our children, the world's children deserve to learn in peace, to live without fear.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Laura Simpson Ryan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/91315362"},{"created_at":"2014-05-09T17:54:25Z","content":"This is important because I go to an all girl school and I care about the education.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Molly Stockmeyer","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/92835644"},{"created_at":"2014-05-12T06:47:53Z","content":"girls are not a object !!! They are no less than boys !!! They need to be treated with respect to !!!!!!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Carine Declercq","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/93564408"},{"created_at":"2014-05-03T18:44:28Z","content":"Children should be safe.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sheree Greenwood","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/791269"},{"created_at":"2014-05-09T18:30:49Z","content":"Education is important for girls","like_count":0,"author_name":"cecilia blanchard","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/92848944"},{"created_at":"2014-05-01T15:25:28Z","content":"Because no one deserves to be exploited","like_count":0,"author_name":"Bukky Adefemi","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/91358235"},{"created_at":"2014-05-11T12:30:33Z","content":"Education is a fundamental right for everyone, education can save a person from decay. While some kids are trying to skip school as often as possible, other kids are striving for knowledge, for making a difference! Bring back our girls \r\nand let them have the privilege of studying, of being themselves, powerful human beings, not slaves!! BRING BACK OUR GIRLS!!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Evelyn Schrauder","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/75328885"},{"created_at":"2014-05-01T02:16:29Z","content":"These are our daughters, they are more valuable than oil!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Tamara Cavell-Allette","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2138589"},{"created_at":"2014-05-01T03:09:01Z","content":"I'd like to make a personal appeal to the First Family to do everything within your power to get out some accurate information about the situation in Chibok Nigeria. Reports are that hundreds of teenage girls have been kidnapped and are potentially being sold into slavery by way of marriage and rape. My hope is that the American Government will take the lead in ensuring justice for these innocent people.\r\n\r\n\"The King will reply, 'Truly I tell you, whatever you did for one of the least of these brothers and sisters of mine, you did for me.\" -Matthew 25:40 ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Leigh Torrence","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/91308713"},{"created_at":"2014-05-06T12:21:51Z","content":"This is an important issue to me because I firmly believe that young women and girls around the world should be free and safe to pursue an education.  And I also believe that any abuse of human rights - regardless of who the victim is - needs to be challenged.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Dennis Hjort","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/91766978"},{"created_at":"2014-05-07T19:05:16Z","content":"It is horrible on how taken girls aren't even important to the Nigerian Government. I want to help.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jennica Hontiveros","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/91944916"},{"created_at":"2014-05-03T02:17:34Z","content":"Who cares?  I care.  This story  should be getting more attention than finding yet another possible lead to the location of a missing plane.  We're helping in the search under the ocean for a missing plane but we can't lend a hand in the search for these children.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kim Davis","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/15659297"},{"created_at":"2014-05-06T23:54:30Z","content":"These young ladies need help ","like_count":0,"author_name":"cindy campbell","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/80423721"},{"created_at":"2014-04-29T13:36:18Z","content":"These 230 girls are waiting in fear for someone to act on their behalf.  Please work for their rescue.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jennifer Carey","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/28501285"},{"created_at":"2014-05-02T16:51:46Z","content":"I have family and friends in Africa! ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Joanne Hall","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/91463133"},{"created_at":"2014-05-05T17:49:30Z","content":"Everyone on this planet is family - these daughters are my daughters and sisters.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Elizabeth Hunter","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3219323"},{"created_at":"2014-05-12T07:42:13Z","content":"Because every human being deserves respect and freedom! People can NEVER decide for others, especially not for reasons that don't support the other's well being!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Wendy Slenders","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/93573056"},{"created_at":"2014-05-02T14:22:10Z","content":"These girls are important assets to their families, Nigerians, Africans, and the world as a whole. This madness must stop! They have their right to life, freedom of movement and right to education!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Derrick Amoako","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/91450677"},{"created_at":"2014-05-09T20:03:18Z","content":"FREEDOM AND WOMEN","like_count":0,"author_name":"jeanniery gonzalez","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/54855673"},{"created_at":"2014-05-01T17:33:01Z","content":"No one should have their freedom taken from them...especially children!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Rita Houston","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/91370097"},{"created_at":"2014-05-13T09:09:18Z","content":"Girls also have a right to be educated and be safe with school and their families.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Tsukushi Okada","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/92590964"},{"created_at":"2014-05-09T22:11:17Z","content":"It is only right that the United States help those who want the freedom to have knowledge and we need to stand up against groups who want to attack innocent, peaceful young women.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Leslie Beery","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/92921644"},{"created_at":"2014-05-02T08:47:58Z","content":"it saddens me that we have to sign a petition for someone to help but i'll sign all the petitions in the world for their freedom. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"steph medina","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/45719457"},{"created_at":"2014-05-02T13:07:35Z","content":"Because these girls are our daughters and need our help and protection!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Rose Boyd","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/15903712"},{"created_at":"2014-05-06T19:55:13Z","content":"Because no man, woman, or child should ever be in fear of being educated or going to school.","like_count":0,"author_name":"KaitLyn Griggs","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/91803561"},{"created_at":"2014-05-02T20:10:49Z","content":"Girls and women COUNT!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lana Nieves","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2475592"},{"created_at":"2014-05-07T18:00:13Z","content":"Is it not our mission and calling to protect the innocent and those unable to speak or defend themselves? Freedom for all!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Katie Morford","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/91927182"},{"created_at":"2014-05-01T20:17:21Z","content":"We have to do this!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Carl Wilkens","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1138659"},{"created_at":"2014-05-03T22:11:17Z","content":"Safe and accessible education of women is crucial to health and economic development in the underdeveloped world.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Tyler McGrady","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/91565379"},{"created_at":"2014-05-08T22:40:40Z","content":"Because EVERYONE regardless of race, gender, sexuality, whatever.... should be able to go to school to learn WITHOUT FEAR. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Maddie Murphy","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/84360317"},{"created_at":"2014-05-06T15:34:11Z","content":"This is about human rights and freedom from slavery. Women are not commodities to be sold or bargained over. From Corona del Mar high school to Nigeria, women/girls must have the right to education, and self determination.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Melissa Badalian","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/788964"},{"created_at":"2014-05-09T19:36:07Z","content":"This is a heartbreaking situation and no one deserves this #bringbackourgirls","like_count":0,"author_name":"Crystal Reed","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/92871856"},{"created_at":"2014-05-09T15:04:19Z","content":"I'm a mother of 2 daughters!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Yakima Johnson","author_url":"http://api.c